/// Steps to download grafana

Step1 : sudo apt update
	sudo apt upgrade
	sudo apt install -y software-properties-common
	this keeps our software upto date

Step2 : sudo add-apt-repository "deb https://packages.grafana.com/oss/deb stable main"
	Grafana provides an official APT repository that you can add to your system.
	
Step3 : curl https://packages.grafana.com/gpg.key | sudo apt-key add -
	Download and install the GPG key for the repository to ensure the packages are trusted.

Step4 : sudo apt update
	After adding the repository, update your APT package list to include the Grafana packages.

Step5 : sudo apt install grafana
	Now, you can install Grafana using the following command:]

Step6 : sudo systemctl start grafana-server
	Start the servicee

Step7 : On web browser run this url 
	http://localhost:3000

Step8 : By default username and password is admin we can change the password later 

Stpe9 : Login with above credentials initially(username and password : admin) then change password.
